Or, \(\cfrac{1}{R^{\prime}}=\cfrac{10}{R}+\cfrac{10}{R}+\ldots \ldots .\)

Or, \(\cfrac{1}{R^{\prime}}=10 \times \cfrac{10}{R}\)

\(\therefore \quad R^{\prime}=\cfrac{R}{100}=0.01 R\)

quest_title: The strongest reducing agent of the alkali metal is
explanation_txt: Li is stronger reducing agent compare to other elements. explanation_txt:
At \(30^{\circ}\),
\(\mathrm{T}_{1}=\cfrac{m v^{2}}{r}+\mathrm{mg} \cos 30^{\circ}\)

At \(60^{\circ}\),
\(\mathrm{T}_{2}=\cfrac{m v^{2}}{r}+\mathrm{mg} \cos 60^{\circ}\)

Here, \(\cos 30^{\circ}>\cos 60^{\circ}\) so
\(\mathrm{T}_{1}>\mathrm{T}_{2}\)

quest_title: A vibration magnetometer consists of two identical bar magnets placed one over the other perpendicularly such that the period of oscillation in a horizontal magnetic field 2\({}^{5/4}\) second. One of the magnets is removed and if the other magnet oscillates in the same field, then the time period in second is
explanation_txt:
From figure, dipole moment of combination

\(M^{\prime}=\sqrt{2} M\)

The total moment of inertia of combination

\(I^{\prime}=I+I=2 I\)

\(T^{\prime}=2 \pi \sqrt{\cfrac{I^{\prime}}{M^{\prime} B_{H}}} \Rightarrow T^{\prime} \propto \sqrt{\cfrac{I^{\prime}}{M^{\prime}}}\)

When one is removed, then \(T \propto \sqrt{\cfrac{I}{M}}\)

\(\cfrac{T^{\prime}}{T}=\sqrt{\cfrac{1}{M} \times \cfrac{\sqrt{2} M}{2 I}} \\ \text { or, } \cfrac{T^{\prime}}{2^{5 / 4}} =\cfrac{1}{2^{1 / 4}} \\ \text { or, } T^{\prime}=2 s \)
